                The cost to repair a dishwasher can vary widely depending on several factors, including the nature of the problem, the brand of the appliance, and your location. On average, a service call to diagnose the issue can range from <b>$75 to $150</b>. This initial fee typically covers the first visit and basic troubleshooting to identify the problem. If parts need to be replaced or more extensive repairs are required, the total cost can increase significantly. For instance, replacing a faulty motor or water pump can cost anywhere from <b>$200 to $600</b>, while more minor repairs, such as fixing a door latch, might only add <b>$50 to $100</b> to the service call fee.
              </p>

              <p>
                Given the potential expenses, it's important to weigh the cost of repairs against the price of purchasing a new dishwasher. Most dishwashers have a lifespan of around 10-15 years, so if your machine is approaching this age, it might be more cost-effective to invest in a new appliance rather than continually paying for repairs. Additionally, frequent breakdowns can lead to more hand washing and inconvenience, not to mention the risk of water damage to your floor if the dishwasher is not operating correctly. Regular maintenance and prompt attention to minor issues can help extend the life of your dishwasher and reduce the likelihood of needing costly repairs.
              </p>
