              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Built-in dishwashers</h3>
                <p>
                  Are the most common type, installed under the kitchen counter and integrated into the cabinetry. They offer a seamless look and can handle large loads. Common repair needs include addressing clogged filters, malfunctioning spray arms, and drainage issues. Periodic checks for leaks and ensuring that the door seals properly can prevent more serious problems. Regular maintenance, such as cleaning the filter and running a self-cleaning cycle, helps keep them running efficiently.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Drawer dishwashers</h3>
