                  Interior lights that donâ€™t work can be due to blown bulbs, faulty door switches, or control board issues. A blown light bulb is the most straightforward problem to fix. If the door switch is defective, it might not signal the lights to turn on when the door is opened. Control board malfunctions can also affect the lighting. Replacing blown bulbs and inspecting door switches and control boards can restore interior lighting functionality.
